description: Questions regarding the Pre-Admission Evaluation (PAE) and Medical Eligibility should be directed here.
Questions regarding Medicaid Financial Eligibility should be directed here.
Managed Care Organizations (MCOs) can help members apply for Long Term Services and Supports (LTSS) programs or answer questions about current benefits and services.
Questions regarding the Pre-Admission Screening and Resident Review (PASRR) process should be directed here.

The Program of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly (PACE) provides comprehensive medical and social services to certain frail, community-dwelling elderly individuals, most of whom are dually eligible for Medicare and Medicaid benefits. Questions regarding PACE should be directed here.
Your local Area Agency on Aging and Disability (AAAD) can provide information and assistance to apply for the CHOICES program.
Department of Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities (DIDD) can provide information and assistance to apply for Employment & Community First CHOICES and the 1915(c) HCBS Waivers.
